-NsGRXIUeL1q-72I9uOv.title: Element
-NsGRXIUeL1q-72I9uOv.definition: An HTML element is a component of an HTML document that tells a web browser how to structure and interpret a part of the HTML document

-NsGRkXnGYrGLTPvNhiR.title: Object
-NsGRkXnGYrGLTPvNhiR.definition: An object is a collection of properties, and a property is an association between a name (or key) and a value. A property's value can be a function, in which case the property is known as a method.

-NsGTRRjAeg4Umxh66ju.title: Properties
-NsGTRRjAeg4Umxh66ju.definition: Properties are defined within selectors by defining a property and a value. They are separated with a colon and delineated with a semi-colon.
